Officials are working with the SAPS to ensure services continue in the afternoon. CAPE TOWN - Golden Arrows says extra security measures have been implemented following a stoning incident on Monday morning.Several of the service's coaches in Mitchells Plain have been stoned.Officials are working with the SAPS to ensure services continue in the afternoon.The bus service's Bronwen Dyke-Beyer says the motive behind the attack is still unclear. At this stage, the motive is unknown, and we are in the process of verifying two injuries. As a precautionary measure, we will have operational staff at the scene, going forward. Anyone with any information regarding these incidents is encouraged to come forward. 